node.text:
20 years ago my Mom & Dad got me a @rushrandle foilboard. It was a dream come true! Up until then I was borrowing my uncles board with size 11 boots. I was so lucky to grow up on Maui during the era when so many water sports were being invented / innovated. 💯
📸 @jdphotofairy

node.text:
2011 I wanted all the smoke 💨 
Paddling on my 8’10” at Te’ahupoo as the swell hit just before dark. Somehow didn’t hit the bottom, but I did take 5 waves on the head on the right and lost my paddle forever. Totally worth it 😎🤘🏾
📸 @benthouard 

@hurley @redbull @tagheuer @gopro @cariuma @ktsurfing

Photo by Kai Lenny on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, body of water and text.

node.text:
I am stoked to be joining the @ouraring team! 
I push myself as hard as I can everyday and for years I only relied on my morning heart rate and how I felt when I woke up. Where is now, I’m able to be super analytical and learn things about myself I didn’t even know. It helps me figure out how hard I should push or how much recovery I need. It has been a great tool for helping me achieve my best! 💯 #ouraring 
Pics: @zaknoyle
